In this project two databases are used.
Both are running as a docker container.

To start project:
    1) download and install docker
    2) pull mysql: and mongodb:latest images
    3) docker container run --name mysql -p 3306 -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD="anypassword" -d mysql:8
       docker container run --name mongodb -p 27017 -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME="anyuser" -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD="anypass
       -e MONGO_INITDB_DATABASE="anydb -d mongodb
    4) connect to mysql db and run mysql-script file
    5) connect to mongodb
    6) change application.properties settings to your database setting
    7) download and install apache tomcat
    8) configure apache tomcat
    9) download and install apache maven
    10) open project as a maven project
    11) run mvn clean
           mvn package
           mvn install
    12) run project


Used technologies:
    BackEnd
  Java SE 8
  Java EE
  Spring framework
  Hibernate
  JPA
  JPQL
  Maven
  Docker
  Maven

    FrontEnd
   Html 5
   Css 3
   Angular 4

    Version Control
         Git